items.title: Wall Street ends with weekly gains as trade negotiations, earnings in focus
items.description: The Dow Jones Industrial Average rose 20.10 points, or 0.05%, to 40,113.50, the S&P 500 gained 40.44 points, or 0.74%, to 5,525.21 and the Nasdaq Composite gained 216.90 points, or 1.26%, to 17,382.94.

items.title: These smallcaps yielded double-digit returns despite indices' muted performance
items.description: As long as the market is trading below 24100/79300, the correction wave is likely to continue. On the downside, the market could slip to 23800/78500, and further downside may drag the index down to 23700/78200, says Amol Athawale, VP-Technical Research, Kotak Securities.

items.title: Market extends gains in second week despite geopolitical tensions
items.description: The Indian rupee ended marginally lower against the US dollar at 85.44 per dollar on April 25 against the April 17 closing of 85.37.
